songs.title: You Make Me Laugh

annotatable.link_title: You Make Me Laugh by Klima
annotatable.title: You Make Me Laugh

songs.lyrics:
Whatever you may say
I think I've made up my mind
This time you know you have to let me
Take care of all the things you keep inside

And if you find me intrusive
It doesn't matter to me
You need someone by your side
And I volunteer for your sake

Please you have to let me
It will all go easy
I'll show you the right way
And you'll make me laugh

Why don't you come with me?
I think that we would be fine
In a little place by the sea
Where we'd watch every day drift by

And if we feel sad and low
Well we could just drink it away
And sing the songs that we like
Out loud to the roaring waves

Please you have to trust me
It will all go easy
I'll show you the right way
And you'll make me laugh

And you'll make me laugh

songs.embed_content: Read “The City” by Klima on Genius
songs.title: The City
songs.lyrics:
Tears always in the city
And they never seem to leave me alone
City's grey, the city's grey
And it's a pity that you're no longer coming around

Oh, I feel the missing bad
All the joy you took it back
I wish you could lie to me
It's so hard to live without certainty

I want you here in the city
You don't want me there anyway
But the time, I know, will come
When you love again shines on

Tears always in the city
Tears always in the city

songs.lyrics:
There's a place in me that belongs to you
And it's here in my breast
Every time that you're away
It bleeds and it bleeds again

Come here
And dance with me
Even if we know
It's the last dance

You can smile
And talk to me
I will stay quiet

It's over

songs.lyrics:
His words will never leave your troubled mind

But if you fear something enough
You can for sure make it happen

You will for sure make it happen

Oh Sylvia

I love that day we spent together
Bags full of chocolate candles

annotatable.link_title: I Will Remember You by Klima
annotatable.title: I Will Remember You

songs.lyrics:
There's dust on your thoughts, you've lost your words again
The moth made a hole the size of your memory
You recall the names but the faces are all wrong
You gave me your hand but your voice stays done

Your last photograph is buried in the sand
Beneath your straw hat and a golden ring
You smile at the mirror like you're smiling at a friend
You smile at the mirror again and again

Who are you?
Who am I?
I will remember you
I will keep you in my heart

I've always liked the way that you do your hair
The white and the grey make your blue eyes so blue
It's almost as if you are waiting for the man
To take you out and go dancing, dancing

Who are you?
Who am I?
I will remember you
I will keep you in my heart
